<i>hi-Lili, hi-Lili, hi-lo, hi-lo
hi-Lili, hi-Lili, hi-lo.</i>

533
00:32:55,218 --> 00:33:01,148
[ Applause and music continues
playing hi-Lili, hi-lo ]

534
00:33:10,979 --> 00:33:16,810
[ Accordian music is heard ]

535
00:33:38,263 --> 00:33:40,174
Here he is now, the boss.

536
00:33:42,267 --> 00:33:43,843
But that's the angry man.

537
00:33:43,878 --> 00:33:45,405
Ha. He's all right.

538
00:33:51,055 --> 00:33:53,998
Now, then, has Jacquot told you?

539
00:33:54,033 --> 00:33:55,321
No, I just fed her.

540
00:33:55,466 --> 00:33:56,549
We're gonna take you on.

541
00:33:56,990 --> 00:33:58,996
We're gonna change the act
and play it for adults.

542
00:33:59,578 --> 00:34:01,271
It'll be a job, fairly steady work.

543
00:34:01,667 --> 00:34:02,946
You'll be paid your share.

544
00:34:04,158 --> 00:34:05,726
Thank you...very much.

545
00:34:08,554 --> 00:34:09,708
What's the matter?

546
00:34:10,842 --> 00:34:12,881
Well...I...I

547
00:34:12,916 --> 00:34:14,919
don't know if...

548
00:34:15,502 --> 00:34:17,203
what...what could I do?

549
00:34:17,792 --> 00:34:19,297
Exactly what you did tonight.

550
00:34:19,906 --> 00:34:21,462
You'll go walking by,

551
00:34:21,741 --> 00:34:22,740
wearing that dress...

552
00:34:22,775 --> 00:34:23,564
mm-hmm.

553
00:34:23,688 --> 00:34:25,283
Hair just as it is...

554
00:34:25,571 --> 00:34:27,524
the puppets will stop you
and speak to you...

555
00:34:27,559 --> 00:34:28,294
mm-hmm.

556
00:34:28,329 --> 00:34:30,233
After that, you'll
talk about anything.

557
00:34:30,553 --> 00:34:33,332
You'll just answer whatever
the puppets happen to say...

558
00:34:33,762 --> 00:34:34,961
The way you did tonight.

559
00:34:36,084 --> 00:34:37,720
- Keep the hi-Lili song in.

560
00:34:37,755 --> 00:34:38,940
I intend to.

561
00:34:39,535 --> 00:34:42,671
We'll agree each night before we start
on the general content of the show.

562
00:34:43,335 --> 00:34:44,905
You'll have to learn
to raise your voice a bit,

563
00:34:44,955 --> 00:34:46,299
and turn to the audience occasionally...

564
00:34:46,511 --> 00:34:47,641
Monsieur Marc,

565
00:34:47,676 --> 00:34:50,382
- Monsieur Marc, hee hee.
I'm staying on.

566
00:34:50,417 --> 00:34:51,144
- [ Giggle ]

567
00:34:51,179 --> 00:34:53,371
The angry man gave me a job.

568
00:34:53,836 --> 00:34:55,105
Isn't that wonderful?

569
00:34:55,285 --> 00:34:56,304
Well, that's great.

570
00:34:57,026 --> 00:34:59,324
- That's fine for everybody, yeah?

571
00:34:59,359 --> 00:35:00,090
Mm-hmm.

572
00:35:00,125 --> 00:35:02,856
Well, you are all set, then.
Be seeing you.

573
00:35:02,974 --> 00:35:03,985
It isn't gonna work.

574
00:35:04,091 --> 00:35:05,773
Sure it is.
It's a great idea.

575
00:35:05,808 --> 00:35:08,722
The little fool isn't interested...
in us or the act.

576
00:35:10,039 --> 00:35:11,147
Oh, but I am.

577
00:35:11,390 --> 00:35:14,338
I love Carrot Top and Reynardo.

578
00:35:14,350 --> 00:35:15,569
We know whom you love.

579
00:35:15,604 --> 00:35:17,249
- Come on.
It's gonna be all right.

580
00:35:17,971 --> 00:35:18,986
- Don't worry.

581
00:35:19,414 --> 00:35:20,715
Find her a place to sleep.

582
00:35:21,302 --> 00:35:23,811
- But, but, he..he's angry,
he said that...

583
00:35:23,846 --> 00:35:26,320
- Don't worry.
Everything will be all right.

584
00:35:29,225 --> 00:35:31,453
Why is Mr. Berthalet so strange?

585
00:35:31,488 --> 00:35:32,323
Because...

586
00:35:33,270 --> 00:35:35,331
because his name
is not Berthalet.

587
00:35:35,777 --> 00:35:38,436
Because he used to be Paul Berthold,
the great dancer.

588
00:35:39,156 --> 00:35:40,818
Because his leg was
injured in the war.

589
00:35:40,853 --> 00:35:42,943
Because now he cannot dance
and has to be a puppeteer,

590
00:35:43,835 --> 00:35:45,675
and doesn't always like it.

591
00:35:47,203 --> 00:35:50,144
But you must never,
never speak to him about it.

592
00:35:50,823 --> 00:35:51,692
Come on now.

593
00:35:54,913 --> 00:35:55,613
Here we are.

594
00:36:02,791 --> 00:36:04,614
There's a little room
back here you can use.

595
00:36:08,276 --> 00:36:09,455
Will he let me stay?

596
00:36:09,694 --> 00:36:10,426
You'll stay.

597
00:36:10,785 --> 00:36:12,797
The truth is, he's very excited
about the idea

598
00:36:12,832 --> 00:36:14,613
of having a new kind of show.

599
00:36:14,850 --> 00:36:16,130
You'll work well with him.

600
00:36:16,384 --> 00:36:18,718
Oh, but I didn't
know I was working.

601
00:36:20,504 --> 00:36:23,520
Well, you...you're giving me
your room.

602
00:36:23,719 --> 00:36:25,595
There's another place
back there for me.

603
00:36:25,689 --> 00:36:28,916
Now go to bed, sleep well,
and dream of magicians,

604
00:36:29,221 --> 00:36:30,514
beautiful magicians.

605
00:36:57,868 --> 00:37:02,281
[ Rhythmic clapping ]

606
00:38:15,612 --> 00:38:17,113
[Clap ]

607
00:41:36,484 --> 00:41:37,576
[ Door closes ]

608
00:41:37,944 --> 00:41:40,489
- [ Jacquot ]  Stop slamming doors.
Be quiet. The girl's asleep.

609
00:41:41,612 --> 00:41:42,719
- [ Paul ]  Do you think I'm drunk?

610
00:41:43,263 --> 00:41:44,406
- [ Jacquot ]  I know you're drunk.

611
00:41:47,436 --> 00:41:48,304
- Let's open a bottle.

612
00:41:48,339 --> 00:41:49,173
- You've had enough.

613
00:41:49,575 --> 00:41:50,473
What makes you think so?

614
00:41:50,508 --> 00:41:52,376
- Go to bed.
Tomorrow is another day.

615
00:41:52,744 --> 00:41:55,130
Oh, now there's
a profound statement.

616
00:41:55,538 --> 00:41:56,574
That's a gem...

617
00:41:57,288 --> 00:41:59,141
"Tomorrow is another day."

618
00:41:59,719 --> 00:42:00,629
And tomorrow...

619
00:42:01,348 --> 00:42:03,380
and tomorrow and tomorrow
with the audience.

620
00:42:03,415 --> 00:42:05,412
That audience, those
endless little faces

621
00:42:05,447 --> 00:42:06,901
alike as mothballs.

622
00:42:07,322 --> 00:42:08,070
I hate 'em!

623
00:42:08,345 --> 00:42:09,887
You don't hate them.

624
00:42:11,274 --> 00:42:12,278
My head aches.

625
00:42:12,744 --> 00:42:13,777
That's not my fault.

626
00:42:13,812 --> 00:42:15,047
I've had too much to drink.

627
00:42:15,814 --> 00:42:17,116
I'll get you some coffee.

628
00:42:18,851 --> 00:42:23,461
Now...why is it that when a man
goes to great effort and expense

629
00:42:23,496 --> 00:42:24,321
to get drunk,

630
00:42:24,356 --> 00:42:26,719
his friends,
instead of respecting this endeavor,

631
00:42:26,754 --> 00:42:29,082
do everything they can
to sober him up?
Why?

632
00:42:29,117 --> 00:42:29,945
Why?

633
00:42:31,887 --> 00:42:33,083
Because they mean well.

634
00:42:34,363 --> 00:42:35,705
Because they're nice people?

635
00:42:37,668 --> 00:42:39,166
I love all people.

636
00:42:39,652 --> 00:42:40,810
You said you hated them.

637
00:42:41,110 --> 00:42:42,830
Well, it wasn't true.

638
00:42:43,212 --> 00:42:44,123
I love them...

639
00:42:44,994 --> 00:42:47,259
the helpless people
who live on the earth,

640
00:42:47,294 --> 00:42:49,419
draw their comfort from it.

641
00:42:50,684 --> 00:42:52,205
Sometimes from each other.

642
00:42:56,259 --> 00:42:57,239
- What have we here?

643
00:42:59,544 --> 00:43:01,063
A girl in love.

644
00:43:01,175 --> 00:43:02,034
Try this.

645
00:43:03,316 --> 00:43:05,071
It's a good thing
to be in love I'm told.

646
00:43:07,797 --> 00:43:11,109
I'm told it's a matter...
not of what you love,

647
00:43:11,581 --> 00:43:13,306
but of how you love...

648
00:43:14,132 --> 00:43:16,464
and that a little of
what you really want

649
00:43:16,748 --> 00:43:19,443
is better than large quantities
of what you don't.

650
00:43:21,201 --> 00:43:23,461
As for me, I want all.

651
00:43:25,100 --> 00:43:27,080
Refusal to compromise.

652
00:43:28,590 --> 00:43:30,353
A sign of immaturity, you know?

653
00:43:30,516 --> 00:43:32,438
Wait! Wait.

654
00:43:35,577 --> 00:43:37,463
Ladies and gentlemen...

655
00:43:37,696 --> 00:43:40,180
I shall now perform
a double pirouette.
- Paul...

656
00:43:40,215 --> 00:43:41,199
[ Thud ]

657
00:43:41,234 --> 00:43:43,102
[ Bangs wall ]

658
00:43:52,693 --> 00:43:53,634
How do you do?

659
00:43:54,496 --> 00:43:56,086
I'm paul Berthalet...

660
00:43:56,721 --> 00:43:57,923
half man...

661
00:43:58,806 --> 00:44:00,524
half mountebank...

662
00:44:00,905 --> 00:44:02,338
disenchanted,

663
00:44:02,716 --> 00:44:03,770
dispossessed,

664
00:44:04,730 --> 00:44:07,639
but going on like
a dog chasing a stick...

665
00:44:07,674 --> 00:44:08,697
a lame dog...

666
00:44:09,238 --> 00:44:12,275
trying to run like the others,
but not getting there.

667
00:44:15,785 --> 00:44:17,636
Oh, well, anyway.

668
00:44:21,582 --> 00:44:23,236
I...I'm sure you're wrong.

669
00:44:23,271 --> 00:44:25,342
I'm sure Reynardo never steals.

670
00:44:25,377 --> 00:44:26,911
Never steals? Hah!

671
00:44:27,057 --> 00:44:29,685
Well, you know my diamond comb,
the one I always wear?

672
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:32,418
But, I had it on the dresser
the other day. I was going to put it on.

673
00:44:32,510 --> 00:44:34,928
I reached for it, and out of the
corner of my eye,

674
00:44:34,963 --> 00:44:36,534
I looked up and suddenly...

675
00:44:36,705 --> 00:44:38,696
Oh! There, you see?

676
00:44:38,709 --> 00:44:41,322
Well, Reynardo, shame on you.

677
00:44:41,357 --> 00:44:43,935
Ahem.
Oh, is this yours?

678
00:44:43,970 --> 00:44:44,538
Yes.

679
00:44:44,573 --> 00:44:45,995
Ahem. Sorry.

680
00:44:46,076 --> 00:44:47,369
Oh, well, you know,

681
00:44:47,404 --> 00:44:50,130
he didn't know it was,
it was mine.

682
00:44:50,165 --> 00:44:52,580
[ Audience laughs ]

683
00:44:54,802 --> 00:44:59,029
And then, along came
the biggest one of all.

684
00:44:59,064 --> 00:44:59,501
What!

685
00:44:59,536 --> 00:45:00,631
I don't believe it.

686
00:45:00,829 --> 00:45:02,217
Well, it's true.

687
00:45:02,252 --> 00:45:03,569
I don't believe it.

688
00:45:03,604 --> 00:45:07,919
Well...huh,... come on now,
don't you do that. Ho, ho, ho.

689
00:45:08,282 --> 00:45:11,143
[ Audience laughs ]

690
00:45:29,533 --> 00:45:30,392
That's for you.

691
00:45:31,617 --> 00:45:34,163
- It's getting to be so much.
- That's the way the boss wants it.

692
00:45:34,198 --> 00:45:36,023
Go, buy yourself
something you don't need.

693
00:45:38,086 --> 00:45:38,933
Thank you.

694
00:45:51,990 --> 00:45:53,131
Thank you, Pierre!

695
00:47:05,317 --> 00:47:07,246
Stop making a fool of yourself.

696
00:47:08,304 --> 00:47:10,128
For the first time you have money,
and what do you do?

697
00:47:10,163 --> 00:47:12,315
Stuff yourself with candy
and buy fairway dolls.

698
00:47:12,708 --> 00:47:14,393
Can't you think of
anything better to buy?

699
00:47:14,428 --> 00:47:15,354
Is there nothing you want?

700
00:47:16,328 --> 00:47:19,167
With the whole world to choose from,
isn't there anything you want?

701
00:47:24,838 --> 00:47:27,550
- But if you could have
anything you wanted...anything,

702
00:47:27,585 --> 00:47:31,738
with the whole world to choose from,
what would you ask for?

703
00:47:32,121 --> 00:47:35,149
If you could have anything...an-y-thing...

704
00:47:35,529 --> 00:47:36,403
what would it be?

705
00:47:38,970 --> 00:47:40,813
- Well...I...I don't know.

706
00:47:40,948 --> 00:47:42,075
- I know.

707
00:47:42,110 --> 00:47:43,994
Ice cream!  Ice cream!

708
00:47:44,029 --> 00:47:44,887
- No, no, no.

709
00:47:45,367 --> 00:47:46,991
Pretty curls, like mine.

710
00:47:47,026 --> 00:47:48,616
- What everybody wants...

711
00:47:48,712 --> 00:47:50,681
to be able to steal anything
without being caught.

712
00:47:50,750 --> 00:47:51,696
-Oh!

713
00:47:51,748 --> 00:47:53,940
A pretty blue dress
like mine.

714
00:47:53,965 --> 00:47:57,529
- Wait a minute.
Let her talk. Let Lili talk.

715
00:48:00,650 --> 00:48:02,226
- Well, I...I don't know.

716
00:48:02,756 --> 00:48:04,305
- I know...

717
00:48:04,701 --> 00:48:06,252
I know what you want.

718
00:48:07,239 --> 00:48:09,248
I think you'd like, someday,

719
00:48:09,916 --> 00:48:12,076
to have the feeling
that you're loved...

720
00:48:12,490 --> 00:48:15,083
that somebody cares
what happens to you.

721
00:48:15,954 --> 00:48:18,649
- Aww, I care.

722
00:48:18,720 --> 00:48:20,141
- I care.

723
00:48:20,699 --> 00:48:22,041
- I care.

724
00:48:22,680 --> 00:48:23,764
- I care.

725
00:48:24,436 --> 00:48:25,638
- I care.

726
00:48:26,270 --> 00:48:27,330
- [ Child ]  I care.

727
00:48:28,907 --> 00:48:30,134
- [ Woman ]   I care.

728
00:48:31,044 --> 00:48:32,553
- And I care.

729
00:48:37,101 --> 00:48:38,354
Hey...

730
00:48:38,551 --> 00:48:39,955
hmm?

731
00:48:48,280 --> 00:48:51,028
Well...a new dress.

732
00:48:51,063 --> 00:48:52,312
New shoes.

733
00:48:52,531 --> 00:48:53,568
Very pretty.

734
00:48:53,688 --> 00:48:54,527
Very chic.

735
00:48:54,971 --> 00:48:56,307
Very grown up.

736
00:48:56,577 --> 00:48:57,963
Look at her, Paul.
Isn't she pretty?

737
00:49:01,541 --> 00:49:02,827
Well, say something, you...

738
00:49:03,941 --> 00:49:04,855
...boss.

739
00:49:05,361 --> 00:49:06,848
I don't care what you
wear on the street,

740
00:49:06,883 --> 00:49:08,858
but get back into your
gray dress for the show.

741
00:49:08,893 --> 00:49:11,105
Oh, yes, of course.
I...I...

742
00:49:11,140 --> 00:49:13,230
Lili, go wait for us a minute.
We'll have lunch in the tent.

743
00:49:14,615 --> 00:49:17,715
So, the awkward child is becoming
an attractive dish,

744
00:49:18,158 --> 00:49:19,619
and you don't like it,

745
00:49:20,010 --> 00:49:22,396
because from now on,
there's gonna be competition.

746
00:49:22,626 --> 00:49:24,098
I don't know what
you're talking about.

747
00:49:24,169 --> 00:49:25,495
I think you do.

748
00:49:25,886 --> 00:49:28,073
[ Carousel plays hi-Lili, hi-lo ]

749
00:49:28,502 --> 00:49:29,999
You talk too much, Jacquot.

750
00:49:30,426 --> 00:49:31,675
At times.

751
00:49:32,342 --> 00:49:34,061
What the devil
is the matter with you?

752
00:49:34,487 --> 00:49:35,604
You're in love with the girl,

753
00:49:35,639 --> 00:49:36,950
and she's in love
with someone else.

754
00:49:37,432 --> 00:49:38,783
This sort of thing
happens all the time.

755
00:49:38,818 --> 00:49:40,115
People don't die of love.

756
00:49:40,627 --> 00:49:41,905
You'll recover...

757
00:49:43,140 --> 00:49:45,933
but meanwhile, can't you be
civilized about it?

758
00:49:49,050 --> 00:49:50,276
I'll try.

759
00:49:51,208 --> 00:49:52,433
Come on.
Let's go to lunch.

760
00:49:55,053 --> 00:49:56,042
Hi, Lili!

761
00:49:56,313 --> 00:49:57,373
- Hi, Claude!

762
00:49:58,758 --> 00:50:00,550
- You hear this?
We are famous.

763
00:50:01,358 --> 00:50:03,092
- The whole town's singing it.

764
00:50:03,528 --> 00:50:07,120
- Monsieur Corvier said last night
the orchestra at Hotel Dubois played it.

765
00:50:07,262 --> 00:50:10,975
The people from the hotel are coming
to the carnival to see our show,

766
00:50:11,799 --> 00:50:15,818
to see our little leading lady...
who has a new dress.

767
00:50:16,687 --> 00:50:18,901
Oh, yes. Very nice.

768
00:50:19,515 --> 00:50:20,434
Where did you buy it?

769
00:50:21,105 --> 00:50:23,056
"Last performance tonight"?

770
00:50:23,776 --> 00:50:25,029
What happened?

771
00:50:25,514 --> 00:50:26,703
- Hello!

772
00:50:26,738 --> 00:50:28,105
Rosalie, what's that mean?

773
00:50:28,869 --> 00:50:31,208
Marc had an offer from
the cabaret of the hotel.

774
00:50:31,243 --> 00:50:32,722
The Hotel Dubois?!

775
00:50:33,839 --> 00:50:34,570
Oh, Jacquot,

776
00:50:34,605 --> 00:50:35,940
no more carnivals.

777
00:50:35,975 --> 00:50:37,492
No more living in trailers.

778
00:50:37,921 --> 00:50:40,484
From now on, it's hotels and cabarets.

779
00:50:40,519 --> 00:50:43,971
Cote D'azur, Cannes, Nice,
perhaps even Paris!

780
00:50:44,006 --> 00:50:45,149
The Folies Paris!

781
00:50:45,184 --> 00:50:46,258
Congratulations!

782
00:50:46,293 --> 00:50:47,632
Are you going with Marc?

783
00:50:53,502 --> 00:50:54,565
And why not?

784
00:50:57,815 --> 00:50:59,462
I...just wondered.

785
00:51:00,689 --> 00:51:02,712
You're crazy about
Marc, aren't you?

786
00:51:03,786 --> 00:51:05,679
You and a hundred others.

787
00:51:07,200 --> 00:51:08,308
Me, too.

788
00:51:19,090 --> 00:51:23,042
Lili dear looks sad
tonight. Why?

789
00:51:23,077 --> 00:51:24,581
Her lover's going away.

790
00:51:24,771 --> 00:51:27,492
-Her lover's going away.
- I have no lover!

791
00:51:27,527 --> 00:51:28,391
Why, you foolish child.

792
00:51:28,426 --> 00:51:30,092
Every girl should have several.

793
00:51:30,214 --> 00:51:32,487
He wouldn't be leaving
if you knew how to hold a man.

794
00:51:32,569 --> 00:51:33,845
But he isn't leaving me.

795
00:51:33,880 --> 00:51:35,121
- [Reynardo ]
Naturally.

796
00:51:36,049 --> 00:51:38,720
No one could leave
my lovely Lili.

797
00:51:39,377 --> 00:51:40,575
He's staying.

798
00:51:41,048 --> 00:51:44,253
No. He-he's going,
but he isn't leaving me.

799
00:51:44,288 --> 00:51:46,925
- [Golo ]  Oh?
You're going with him?

800
00:51:46,960 --> 00:51:47,799
No.

801
00:51:47,834 --> 00:51:48,549
Why not?

802
00:51:49,255 --> 00:51:50,791
Because he didn't ask her.

803
00:51:51,160 --> 00:51:53,207
Well, an experienced woman
knows how to make the man ask her.

804
00:51:54,013 --> 00:51:55,021
Ask her what?

805
00:51:55,056 --> 00:51:56,391
- [ Reynardo ]
That depends.

806
00:51:57,028 --> 00:52:00,038
Now, what do you
want him to ask you?

807
00:52:00,139 --> 00:52:01,781
I didn't say
I wanted him to...

808
00:52:03,288 --> 00:52:03,867
You see,

809
00:52:03,902 --> 00:52:05,321
-  he isn't my...
- Oh, really!

810
00:52:05,356 --> 00:52:06,583
She doesn't make sense.

811
00:52:06,618 --> 00:52:07,811
How can I when you...

812
00:52:07,880 --> 00:52:09,373
- [Carrot Top ]
Now you're making her cry.

813
00:52:09,686 --> 00:52:10,470
Poor girl.

814
00:52:10,860 --> 00:52:12,326
She's been throwing
herself at the man,

815
00:52:12,361 --> 00:52:14,767
and he doesn't know she's alive.

816
00:52:15,010 --> 00:52:15,829
But he does.

817
00:52:16,012 --> 00:52:17,890
He's been very kind to me.

818
00:52:18,167 --> 00:52:20,096
He's the only one who ever was...

819
00:52:20,537 --> 00:52:23,070
except you, but now even you...

820
00:52:24,749 --> 00:52:27,072
Please, let's talk about something else.

821
00:52:27,443 --> 00:52:28,273
- [Carrot Top ]
I know.

822
00:52:28,360 --> 00:52:29,645
We'll sing for you.

823
00:52:30,371 --> 00:52:31,158
Ahem.

824
00:52:31,438 --> 00:52:38,165
<i>A song of love is a gay song,
hi-Lili, hi-Lili, hi-lo.</i>

825
00:52:38,218 --> 00:52:44,996
<i>A song of love is a song of joy,
A waltz for girl and boy.</i>

826
00:52:45,006 --> 00:52:51,683
<i>[ Golo ]  A song of love is a gay song,
for we're in love, and it's so.</i>

827
00:52:51,718 --> 00:52:57,934
<i>hi-Lili, hi-Lili, hi-lo, hi-lo,
hi-Lili, hi-Lili, hi-lo.</i>

828
00:52:57,969 --> 00:53:10,689
<i>hi-Lili, hi-Lili, hi-lo, hi-lo,
hi-Lili, hi-Liliiiii...hi-lo.</i>

829
00:53:10,724 --> 00:53:12,155
[ Applause ] Well!

830
00:53:12,190 --> 00:53:14,253
Oh, thank you.

831
00:53:14,640 --> 00:53:15,621
Thank you so much.

832
00:53:25,206 --> 00:53:27,415
- [ Rosalie ]  It's going to be
very different now.

833
00:53:27,635 --> 00:53:29,500
It wasn't so bad
all these years

834
00:53:29,535 --> 00:53:31,335
when you were mad about
women who didn't count.

835
00:53:31,370 --> 00:53:33,473
And anyhow, we were
always on the move,

836
00:53:33,508 --> 00:53:35,802
and I knew you had to leave
them sooner or later.

837
00:53:36,723 --> 00:53:39,427
But now, there's going
to be rich Americans

838
00:53:39,462 --> 00:53:41,838
on the prowl, and smart divorcees.

839
00:53:42,093 --> 00:53:43,591
And that's a different matter.

840
00:53:44,867 --> 00:53:47,255
You'll be a good catch
with money in your pocket,

841
00:53:47,395 --> 00:53:48,622
a great success.

842
00:53:49,183 --> 00:53:52,529
Well, I want these women
to know that you're married

843
00:53:53,304 --> 00:53:54,132
to me.

844
00:53:55,016 --> 00:53:58,248
I'm tired of pretending to be dclass,
when I am not.

845
00:53:58,447 --> 00:54:00,792
- You know it's better
for the act to...

846
00:54:00,827 --> 00:54:01,609
that's nonsense.

847
00:54:01,866 --> 00:54:03,818
You are well enough
established now,

848
00:54:03,853 --> 00:54:06,492
and the act is good enough
to stand on its own.

849
00:54:06,519 --> 00:54:09,275
You don't have to dangle yourself
in front of these women.

850
00:54:09,617 --> 00:54:12,854
From now on, I am telling
everybody that we are married.

851
00:54:13,958 --> 00:54:18,427
Look, I am wearing it, and
I'm going to go on wearing it...

852
00:54:18,462 --> 00:54:20,498
my nice, big, fat golden band.

853
00:54:20,533 --> 00:54:21,961
And you will wear yours.

854
00:54:22,308 --> 00:54:24,147
It has been a secret long enough.

855
00:54:25,411 --> 00:54:27,165
You thought I didn't know
where it was.

856
00:54:27,670 --> 00:54:28,223
Here!

857
00:54:29,873 --> 00:54:30,668
Wear it.

858
00:54:32,467 --> 00:54:34,737
And it wouldn't hurt you
to help me with the trailer.

859
00:54:34,772 --> 00:54:35,594
- Oh.

860
00:54:35,629 --> 00:54:38,464
- We are leaving in a half an hour,
and you are not yet packed.

861
00:54:38,916 --> 00:54:42,882
- Every time we move you disappear
and leave it all to me.

862
00:54:43,352 --> 00:54:45,058
- Well, things are going to change.

863
00:54:45,441 --> 00:54:48,241
- And, Marc, at the hotel...

864
00:54:48,276 --> 00:54:51,447
[Both speaking ]
Would you please watch yourself
on the curtain calls?

865
00:54:51,482 --> 00:54:55,036
You don't have to take your
bows at the center of the stage.

866
00:54:55,071 --> 00:54:57,276
You could move over a little.

867
00:54:57,957 --> 00:55:00,498
You could move over a little.

868
00:55:00,533 --> 00:55:02,442
Hello...Marc.

869
00:55:03,295 --> 00:55:06,109
Well...hello.

870
00:55:08,496 --> 00:55:09,278
Hello.

871
00:55:10,046 --> 00:55:10,804
Hello.

872
00:55:13,698 --> 00:55:15,003
Wh-what are you doing?

873
00:55:16,009 --> 00:55:17,036
Nothing.

874
00:55:19,080 --> 00:55:20,045
How are you?

875
00:55:20,902 --> 00:55:22,270
Very well, thank you.

876
00:55:22,720 --> 00:55:23,489
And you?

877
00:55:24,154 --> 00:55:27,170
Uh...I'm very well, too.

878
00:55:27,286 --> 00:55:28,324
That's good.

879
00:55:28,359 --> 00:55:29,227
Uh-huh.

880
00:55:33,801 --> 00:55:36,488
Uh...would you like
a cup of coffee?

881
00:55:37,423 --> 00:55:38,960
Are you inviting me in?

882
00:55:39,656 --> 00:55:40,316
Yes.

883
00:55:50,214 --> 00:55:50,951
Sit down.

884
00:55:51,798 --> 00:55:53,054
Thank you.

885
00:55:57,418 --> 00:55:59,126
When are you leaving the carnival?

886
00:55:59,812 --> 00:56:02,075
Very soon.
In about an hour.

887
00:56:03,688 --> 00:56:04,836
Rosalie, too?

888
00:56:05,133 --> 00:56:06,161
Uh-huh.

889
00:56:06,906 --> 00:56:08,553
Rosalie's my partner.

890
00:56:09,300 --> 00:56:11,318
Will you come and
see me at the hotel?

891
00:56:12,651 --> 00:56:13,483
May I?

892
00:56:13,518 --> 00:56:14,947
I'd be glad if you do.

893
00:56:15,469 --> 00:56:16,857
It's not very far.

894
00:56:17,389 --> 00:56:19,108
Just at the edge of town.

895
00:56:20,059 --> 00:56:24,176
But...
will your boyfriend let you?

896
00:56:24,211 --> 00:56:24,993
My who?

897
00:56:25,028 --> 00:56:27,379
Your bad-tempered boyfriend.

898
00:56:27,414 --> 00:56:29,621
Oh, he's not my boyfriend.
He hates me.

899
00:56:30,558 --> 00:56:32,746
Carrot Top's my boyfriend.

900
00:56:32,781 --> 00:56:34,934
I thought I was the one...

901
00:56:35,821 --> 00:56:37,391
Oh...you are...

902
00:56:37,426 --> 00:56:38,282
Ah.

903
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:40,256
I...I never see you.

904
00:56:41,140 --> 00:56:42,604
You're seeing me now.

905
00:56:43,821 --> 00:56:45,786
[ Door opens ]

906
00:56:46,368 --> 00:56:47,358
Hello, Paul.

907
00:56:48,287 --> 00:56:50,664
I dropped in to see if you'd like
to buy my trailer.

908
00:56:50,699 --> 00:56:52,537
I won't be needing it anymore.

909
00:56:52,741 --> 00:56:55,437
You are a bit crowded in here,
aren't you?

910
00:56:55,572 --> 00:56:57,062
My trailer is bigger.

911
00:56:57,515 --> 00:57:00,135
How do you manage,
the three of you in this place?

912
00:57:00,217 --> 00:57:02,141
We manage very nicely,
thank you.

913
00:57:02,245 --> 00:57:03,451
I'm sure you do.

914
00:57:03,533 --> 00:57:05,461
Well, I'll be getting on.

915
00:57:05,634 --> 00:57:06,938
Think about the trailer.

916
00:57:07,291 --> 00:57:08,809
You can afford it now.

917
00:57:08,913 --> 00:57:10,840
I hear you're doing very well.

918
00:57:10,875 --> 00:57:12,489
The audiences like Lili.

919
00:57:13,097 --> 00:57:14,559
Can't say I blame them.

920
00:57:15,167 --> 00:57:18,088
Well, come and visit me sometime.

921
00:57:26,063 --> 00:57:27,613
You know what you are,
don't you?

922
00:57:28,765 --> 00:57:31,875
But you're an amateur,
an understudy,

923
00:57:31,910 --> 00:57:33,174
a poor man's version.

924
00:57:33,392 --> 00:57:34,394
But don't be discouraged.

925
00:57:34,429 --> 00:57:36,416
You'll get there because
you're so willing,

926
00:57:36,451 --> 00:57:38,404
and it's the willingness
that counts, isn't it,

927
00:57:38,439 --> 00:57:39,555
in all noble endeavors?

928
00:57:39,624 --> 00:57:40,910
You're starting young,

929
00:57:41,355 --> 00:57:43,488
but you'll be interesting to observe
by the time you're 20.

930
00:57:43,523 --> 00:57:44,928
Let's just hope I don't have to see it!

931
00:57:45,357 --> 00:57:46,663
What do you know about it?

932
00:57:47,014 --> 00:57:48,494
What could you know about love?

933
00:57:48,529 --> 00:57:50,562
Go on, tell me about it.

934
00:57:50,913 --> 00:57:52,455
Nothing makes me sick.

935
00:57:54,735 --> 00:57:55,888
[ Door slams shut ]

936
00:58:16,052 --> 00:58:17,643
Marc! Marc!

937
00:58:17,678 --> 00:58:18,759
Don't be a fool.

938
00:58:18,794 --> 00:58:19,372
Marc!

939
00:58:19,672 --> 00:58:20,345
Stop it!

940
00:58:20,658 --> 00:58:21,762
[ Slap ]

941
00:58:48,291 --> 00:58:49,461
Monsieur Berthalet?

942
00:58:50,840 --> 00:58:51,578
Yes?

943
00:58:51,704 --> 00:58:52,930
Permit me to introduce myself.

944
00:58:52,965 --> 00:58:54,055
Antoine Tonit.

945
00:58:54,841 --> 00:58:55,605
How do you do?

946
00:58:55,800 --> 00:58:57,362
My associate, Monsieur Erique.

947
00:58:57,404 --> 00:58:58,731
How do you do, monsieur?

948
00:58:58,766 --> 00:58:59,470
May we sit down?

949
00:59:05,742 --> 00:59:06,985
Haven't we met before?

950
00:59:07,182 --> 00:59:08,426
I think not.

951
00:59:08,461 --> 00:59:09,671
Berthalet...

952
00:59:09,699 --> 00:59:11,073
Paul Berthalet...

953
00:59:11,862 --> 00:59:13,904
Of course.
The name is different, but...

954
00:59:13,939 --> 00:59:16,504
Ah.
Paul Berthold, the dancer.

955
00:59:17,793 --> 00:59:18,801
Not anymore.

956
00:59:19,030 --> 00:59:21,872
Yes, of course.
Just before the war.

957
00:59:22,624 --> 00:59:24,892
Your first recital was a sensation.

958
00:59:24,927 --> 00:59:25,860
Then you disappeared.

959
00:59:26,439 --> 00:59:27,342
I went into the army.

960
00:59:27,377 --> 00:59:28,282
But afterward?

961
00:59:28,908 --> 00:59:31,850
Afterward, I preferred
the fresh air of carnivals.

962
00:59:32,265 --> 00:59:35,879
I preferred the dear faces
of little children with runny noses.

963
00:59:36,033 --> 00:59:36,666
Hmm.

964
00:59:37,002 --> 00:59:38,587
You've hit on a great idea,

965
00:59:38,622 --> 00:59:39,233
No, thank you.

966
00:59:39,297 --> 00:59:42,701
combining the live figure
with the puppets.

967
00:59:42,736 --> 00:59:43,791
Where did you find the girl?

968
00:59:44,942 --> 00:59:47,578
We can't make up our minds,
whether she's a superb actress

969
00:59:47,613 --> 00:59:49,492
or you're a svengali.

970
00:59:50,499 --> 00:59:51,113
Neither.

971
00:59:53,988 --> 01:00:00,332
No...she's like a little bell
that gives off a pure sound

972
01:00:00,367 --> 01:00:01,761
no matter how you strike it,

973
01:00:02,621 --> 01:00:06,512
because she is in herself
so good and true and pure.

974
01:00:08,235 --> 01:00:11,280
She lives each show,
loves it.

975
01:00:12,633 --> 01:00:15,771
Those moments with the puppets
are her happiest, I'll venture to say.

976
01:00:15,928 --> 01:00:17,469
- I'll venture to agree.

977
01:00:19,516 --> 01:00:23,089
We've...we've worked out
a basic formula...

978
01:00:23,124 --> 01:00:23,549
- [ Jacquot ]
Paul.

979
01:00:23,584 --> 01:00:26,174
- and within that framework,
we try and develop

980
01:00:26,209 --> 01:00:27,696
- a new show every day...
- Paul, could you come back

981
01:00:27,731 --> 01:00:29,280
- with me to the tent, please?

982
01:00:29,315 --> 01:00:30,830
Uh...My associate, Jacquot.

983
01:00:30,924 --> 01:00:31,665
Monsieur...

984
01:00:31,700 --> 01:00:32,160
- Tonit.

985
01:00:32,195 --> 01:00:34,060
- I'm sorry, I..
- We like your act.

986
01:00:34,095 --> 01:00:34,693
Thank you.

987
01:00:34,791 --> 01:00:36,499
If you can hold these
carnival audiences,

988
01:00:36,534 --> 01:00:37,402
you can hold any.

989
01:00:37,512 --> 01:00:39,267
The Folies de Paris will be easy.

990
01:00:39,425 --> 01:00:40,727
Sure. We'll try it tomorrow.

991
01:00:40,762 --> 01:00:42,567
Well, not tomorrow, perhaps,
but we'd like you

992
01:00:42,602 --> 01:00:44,380
to be ready to open
in about two weeks.

993
01:00:45,479 --> 01:00:46,170
Two weeks?

994
01:00:47,491 --> 01:00:48,360
Tonit?

995
01:00:48,855 --> 01:00:50,639
You're Antoine Tonit
of the Folies Paris!

996
01:00:50,674 --> 01:00:52,034
I'm sorry.
I thought I'd told you.

997
01:00:52,069 --> 01:00:54,286
- Tonit and Erique.
- As for the details of the contract,

998
01:00:54,321 --> 01:00:55,926
if you'll come back
to the hotel with us now...

999
01:00:55,961 --> 01:00:56,772
fine.

1000
01:00:56,807 --> 01:00:57,982
We'll have to let you know.

1001
01:00:58,017 --> 01:00:59,526
We can't accept now.

1002
01:00:59,561 --> 01:01:01,144
But you have no contract here.

1003
01:01:01,179 --> 01:01:01,875
You're free.

1004
01:01:01,910 --> 01:01:02,572
Completely.

1005
01:01:02,651 --> 01:01:03,578
We'll have to let you know.

1006
01:01:03,613 --> 01:01:04,624
But we know now.

1007
01:01:04,659 --> 01:01:06,443
I'm sorry.
We have to talk about this.

1008
01:01:06,619 --> 01:01:07,539
By all means...

1009
01:01:07,574 --> 01:01:08,802
What do we have
to talk over?

1010
01:01:09,048 --> 01:01:10,875
But don't dismiss
this offer too lightly.

1011
01:01:11,034 --> 01:01:13,453
The act is nothing
without the girl.

1012
01:01:13,488 --> 01:01:14,947
I agree.
She's enchanting.

1013
01:01:15,100 --> 01:01:17,211
But this one,
the creativeness is his.

1014
01:01:17,495 --> 01:01:20,145
He has a talent for improvisation
that I've never seen before.

1015
01:01:20,398 --> 01:01:21,605
It's close to genius.

1016
01:01:21,875 --> 01:01:23,588
You've hit on a new career, Berthalet,

1017
01:01:23,623 --> 01:01:26,141
that'll outstrip anything
you could've done as a dancer.

1018
01:01:26,446 --> 01:01:28,267
But you must know this,
or you wouldn't have

1019
01:01:28,302 --> 01:01:29,459
given up your dancing for it.

1020
01:01:30,436 --> 01:01:31,778
I didn't give up anything.

1021
01:01:33,993 --> 01:01:35,907
I became a puppeteer
because it was the only way

1022
01:01:35,942 --> 01:01:37,784
I could earn enough to feed myself.

1023
01:01:38,124 --> 01:01:40,402
You see, a dancer grows
conscious of his body.

1024
01:01:40,437 --> 01:01:42,680
When it'll no longer do
what he wants it to do,

1025
01:01:42,715 --> 01:01:43,855
he grows to hate it.

1026
01:01:44,336 --> 01:01:47,039
So I hid mine behind the curtain
of a puppet stage.

1027
01:01:47,420 --> 01:01:48,991
I'm sorry.
We didn't know.

1028
01:01:49,026 --> 01:01:50,853
We've been tactless, I'm afraid.

1029
01:01:50,888 --> 01:01:54,125
No. You've done the greatest thing
for me you could've done.

1030
01:01:54,952 --> 01:01:56,198
Tell me again what you said.

1031
01:01:56,411 --> 01:01:58,160
You mean that I think
you've chosen a new career

1032
01:01:58,195 --> 01:02:00,250
that'll outstrip anything
you might've done as a dancer?

1033
01:02:00,733 --> 01:02:02,935
But you said that before
you knew I was lame.

1034
01:02:03,671 --> 01:02:04,389
You meant it?

1035
01:02:04,424 --> 01:02:05,694
I meant it and more.

1036
01:02:05,848 --> 01:02:07,393
I'll underwrite your new career.

1037
01:02:08,495 --> 01:02:09,368
Thank you.

1038
01:02:10,347 --> 01:02:11,204
Thank you.

1039
01:02:11,320 --> 01:02:12,196
Tomorrow.

1040
01:02:17,629 --> 01:02:19,302
What was that nonsense
about letting them know?

1041
01:02:19,337 --> 01:02:20,975
You think to get more money
out of them by saying

1042
01:02:21,010 --> 01:02:21,685
we're unwilling?

1043
01:02:21,851 --> 01:02:24,674
I said it because I'm not sure
you have an act to sell.

1044
01:02:25,504 --> 01:02:26,578
Lili is leaving.

1045
01:02:27,766 --> 01:02:29,116
What did you do to her?

1046
01:02:30,795 --> 01:02:32,805
Stopped her from making
a fool of herself.

1047
01:02:32,912 --> 01:02:33,731
Leaving?

1048
01:02:34,144 --> 01:02:35,585
That child's an idiot.

1049
01:02:35,620 --> 01:02:37,027
She's not an idiot.

1050
01:02:37,949 --> 01:02:39,709
And she isn't a child any longer.

1051
01:02:40,558 --> 01:02:43,665
She's beginning to realize the fact
that there's cruelty in the world...

1052
01:02:44,187 --> 01:02:46,684
and she's starting
to protect herself from it.

1053
01:02:48,988 --> 01:02:51,361
Well...what do we do now?

1054
01:02:51,396 --> 01:02:53,735
You'll figure it out.

1055
01:02:54,178 --> 01:02:55,609
You're the genius.

1056
01:03:12,158 --> 01:03:13,101
[ Knock knock ]

1057
01:03:13,136 --> 01:03:14,044
[ Marc ]  Come in.

1058
01:03:17,429 --> 01:03:18,520
Well.

1059
01:03:21,622 --> 01:03:23,453
It's all right if Rosie is coming.

1060
01:03:24,648 --> 01:03:26,669
What I have to say
won't take very long.

1061
01:03:28,964 --> 01:03:30,994
Here's something you
lost in the trailer.

1062
01:03:31,029 --> 01:03:31,776
Oh.

1063
01:03:33,057 --> 01:03:36,783
I didn't know at first.
And I wanted to ask you,

1064
01:03:38,456 --> 01:03:40,209
but now I think I know.

1065
01:03:40,973 --> 01:03:41,987
You're married

1066
01:03:42,441 --> 01:03:43,553
to Rosalie.

1067
01:03:44,346 --> 01:03:45,874
I never denied it.

1068
01:03:46,501 --> 01:03:48,191
- No, you didn't.
- Ah.

1069
01:03:48,931 --> 01:03:50,382
And I've been silly.

1070
01:03:52,421 --> 01:03:55,101
But I've put a lot of things
together in my head

1071
01:03:55,136 --> 01:03:56,262
this last half hour.

1072
01:03:56,806 --> 01:04:00,261
A great many things,
back to the day we met.

1073
01:04:01,194 --> 01:04:04,869
I know I've been living in a dream,
just like a little girl...

1074
01:04:06,020 --> 01:04:08,475
without seeing what I didn't
want to see...

1075
01:04:11,090 --> 01:04:13,349
but you want to know
something, Marc?

1076
01:04:15,173 --> 01:04:18,153
We sometimes outgrow
feelings and ideas,

1077
01:04:18,274 --> 01:04:21,471
just like a little girl
outgrows her dresses,

1078
01:04:22,313 --> 01:04:27,159
but somehow, it turns out that
there's a right time for everything...

1079
01:04:27,716 --> 01:04:29,103
in the right order.

1080
01:04:29,895 --> 01:04:33,331
There's a time for going to school.

1081
01:04:34,427 --> 01:04:36,498
A time for losing our parents,

1082
01:04:38,063 --> 01:04:42,592
and a time for falling in love
with a beautiful magician.

1083
01:04:44,640 --> 01:04:46,648
But there's a time for waking up.

1084
01:04:49,779 --> 01:04:53,514
You are a wise girl...Lili.

1085
01:04:53,797 --> 01:04:55,331
Where did you learn all this?

1086
01:04:56,268 --> 01:04:57,384
We don't learn.

1087
01:04:58,047 --> 01:04:59,724
We just get older...

1088
01:05:00,289 --> 01:05:01,454
and we know.

1089
01:05:04,815 --> 01:05:05,861
Good-bye, Marc.

1090
01:05:07,203 --> 01:05:08,489
Good-bye.

1091
01:05:10,647 --> 01:05:12,897
Thank you for your patience.

1092
01:05:14,482 --> 01:05:17,851
Forgive me for having been
such a nuisance.

1093
01:05:27,726 --> 01:05:29,618
Oh, Rosalie,

1094
01:05:30,496 --> 01:05:31,822
I'm...I'm leaving.

1095
01:05:31,857 --> 01:05:34,306
I just said good-bye
to your husband.

1096
01:05:34,588 --> 01:05:35,424
Good-bye.

1097
01:05:48,106 --> 01:05:49,044
Lili?

1098
01:05:49,536 --> 01:05:51,778
Oh, Lili, please, wait a minute.

1099
01:05:52,261 --> 01:05:55,630
Are you gonna leave
without saying good-bye?

1100
01:05:56,221 --> 01:05:59,425
Please, Lili, just for a minute,
come here.

1101
01:06:00,260 --> 01:06:02,817
Please? Closer.

1102
01:06:04,134 --> 01:06:06,053
I have a favor to ask, and

1103
01:06:06,976 --> 01:06:08,915
I don't want the others to hear.

1104
01:06:11,399 --> 01:06:14,921
If you're leaving, Lili,
please take me with you.

1105
01:06:15,568 --> 01:06:18,886
I wanna go with you,
wherever you go.

1106
01:06:19,289 --> 01:06:21,782
It won't be the same
here without you.

1107
01:06:23,789 --> 01:06:25,880
You're my sweetheart, you see?

1108
01:06:26,510 --> 01:06:28,427
It was love at first sight.

1109
01:06:29,273 --> 01:06:33,670
From the first moment I saw you
walking by, wearing that... awful hat,

1110
01:06:34,424 --> 01:06:36,790
and carrying that lopsided suitcase.

1111
01:06:37,123 --> 01:06:40,713
- Please...oh, please don't
leave us, Lili!

1112
01:06:41,017 --> 01:06:44,314
I never had a real friend
until you came along.

1113
01:06:44,564 --> 01:06:46,154
Please take me with you.

1114
01:06:46,728 --> 01:06:48,773
If you really loved us,
you wouldn't go away.

1115
01:06:48,808 --> 01:06:49,678
Oh, but I do.

1116
01:06:49,713 --> 01:06:50,922
It's just that I...

1117
01:06:51,121 --> 01:06:52,109
I'll say it.

1118
01:06:52,324 --> 01:06:53,734
You hate the boss.

1119
01:06:53,920 --> 01:06:55,365
He's unreasonable.

1120
01:06:55,400 --> 01:06:56,459
He's mean.

1121
01:06:56,494 --> 01:06:57,517
He's jealous.

1122
01:06:57,598 --> 01:06:59,277
We'll protect you from him.

1123
01:06:59,292 --> 01:07:00,334
Oh, you always have.

1124
01:07:00,956 --> 01:07:03,040
You've always been
so kind and good...

1125
01:07:04,028 --> 01:07:07,340
- and you seem to know
what's in my heart or

1126
01:07:07,375 --> 01:07:10,652
- what I'm thinking
and what I'm feeling.

1127
01:07:14,692 --> 01:07:15,467
I'll kill him!

1128
01:07:15,651 --> 01:07:19,350
I'm gonna kill the boss! Grrr!

1129
01:07:20,203 --> 01:07:23,319
Well, anyway, I'll give him
a good talking to.

1130
01:07:23,568 --> 01:07:24,828
Hey, boss...

1131
01:07:25,028 --> 01:07:25,938
- Lili?

1132
01:07:26,861 --> 01:07:27,708
Here.

1133
01:07:27,946 --> 01:07:29,956
It's our going-away present.

1134
01:07:30,193 --> 01:07:33,741
Oh, Reynardo...how very nice.

1135
01:07:33,797 --> 01:07:35,430
It was very expensive.

1136
01:07:35,581 --> 01:07:38,309
He probably stole it.
You know Reynardo.

1137
01:07:38,604 --> 01:07:40,309
How did you get it, Reynardo?

1138
01:07:40,344 --> 01:07:42,078
Well, must I tell?

1139
01:07:43,116 --> 01:07:45,802
Reynardo, you promised me
you would never steal again.

1140
01:07:45,837 --> 01:07:47,760
I didn't steal it.

1141
01:07:47,853 --> 01:07:51,512
If you must know, I'm paying for it
on the installment plan.

1142
01:07:51,547 --> 01:07:53,342
What happens if you don't
keep up with the payments?

1143
01:07:53,560 --> 01:07:55,750
I know him.
He'll never keep up.

1144
01:07:55,829 --> 01:07:57,165
They'll come and
take it away from you.

1145
01:07:57,200 --> 01:07:59,709
No, they won't.
I made a deal.

1146
01:08:00,538 --> 01:08:02,116
What sort of a deal?

1147
01:08:02,324 --> 01:08:05,141
Well, I agreed that if I didn't
keep up with the payments,

1148
01:08:05,176 --> 01:08:07,180
I'd give the man something
else in exchange.

1149
01:08:07,215 --> 01:08:08,774
I signed a paper.

1150
01:08:08,809 --> 01:08:10,690
Uh-oh.
He signed a paper.

1151
01:08:10,725 --> 01:08:12,762
What does the man
get in exchange?

1152
01:08:12,959 --> 01:08:14,679
Another fox fur.

1153
01:08:15,179 --> 01:08:16,114
Another?

1154
01:08:16,149 --> 01:08:17,050
Uh-huh...

1155
01:08:18,625 --> 01:08:19,457
me.

1156
01:08:20,382 --> 01:08:22,068
Well, you poor darling.

1157
01:08:22,103 --> 01:08:23,720
- You traded your life

1158
01:08:23,755 --> 01:08:25,645
- to get me a present.
- Mmm.

1159
01:08:26,500 --> 01:08:27,346
Oh, Reynardo, you...

1160
01:08:27,398 --> 01:08:31,161
Trust him to take advantage
of a situation like this.

1161
01:08:31,724 --> 01:08:33,335
I wanna go with you, Lili.

1162
01:08:34,328 --> 01:08:36,277
Why don't you take
us all with you?

1163
01:08:36,867 --> 01:08:38,958
We don't want you
to forget us, Lili.

1164
01:08:38,993 --> 01:08:40,641
I never could forget you.

1165
01:08:40,971 --> 01:08:42,999
You've become so
very dear to me.

1166
01:08:43,805 --> 01:08:45,963
You're the only things I love.

1167
01:08:47,115 --> 01:08:48,670
I know you love me, too.

1168
01:08:51,545 --> 01:08:53,764
Why, you poor darlings,
you're trembling.

1169
01:09:05,410 --> 01:09:06,805
Well, are you staying or going?

1170
01:09:07,547 --> 01:09:08,936
We've had an offer
from the Folies Paris,

1171
01:09:08,936 --> 01:09:10,481
but we can't accept it
without you.

1172
01:09:11,785 --> 01:09:15,825
I've been an idiot,
a stupid fool.

1173
01:09:16,816 --> 01:09:20,348
Melting and sniveling over
Reynardo and Carrot Top.

1174
01:09:21,768 --> 01:09:23,499
I must be crazy.

1175
01:09:24,911 --> 01:09:27,943
They've become
so very dear to me,

1176
01:09:27,943 --> 01:09:32,865
I forget...I forget every time
that it's only you.

1177
01:09:33,817 --> 01:09:34,917
Or is it you?

1178
01:09:36,246 --> 01:09:37,077
Is it?

1179
01:09:37,805 --> 01:09:38,752
Wh-what are you?

1180
01:09:38,752 --> 01:09:42,468
Are you just a monster
without any feeling?

1181
01:09:43,661 --> 01:09:45,555
Why can't you ever say
a kind word?

1182
01:09:46,365 --> 01:09:48,184
Why do you hide
behind those puppets?

1183
01:09:48,184 --> 01:09:49,330
I am the puppets!

1184
01:09:50,737 --> 01:09:55,519
I'm Carrot Top: Confident, clever,
capable of running his life and yours

1185
01:09:55,519 --> 01:09:56,261
and everybody else's.

1186
01:09:56,261 --> 01:09:59,549
And I'm Golo the Giant:
Cowardly, stupid,

1187
01:10:00,040 --> 01:10:02,979
longing to be loved, clumsy,
and in need of comforting.

1188
01:10:03,729 --> 01:10:08,913
And I'm Marguerite, too:
Vain, jealous, obsessed with self,

1189
01:10:08,913 --> 01:10:10,521
looking at my face in the mirror.

1190
01:10:10,521 --> 01:10:13,131
Are my teeth nice?
Is my hair growing thin?

1191
01:10:13,878 --> 01:10:17,665
And I'm Reynardo
the thief, the opportunist,

1192
01:10:17,665 --> 01:10:19,177
full of compromise and lies.

1193
01:10:19,177 --> 01:10:21,198
Like any other man, I have in me
all these things,

1194
01:10:21,392 --> 01:10:23,374
all of these and
as many more again.

1195
01:10:23,902 --> 01:10:25,978
Must I make a new puppet
for the small part of me

1196
01:10:25,978 --> 01:10:26,975
you've managed to see?

1197
01:10:27,367 --> 01:10:28,129
The monster?

1198
01:10:28,129 --> 01:10:29,013
The angry man?

1199
01:10:29,739 --> 01:10:32,502
The frustrated dancer, clumping along
with a leg anchored to the ground,

1200
01:10:32,502 --> 01:10:33,825
and a heart anchored to...

1201
01:10:41,612 --> 01:10:43,700
but you don't have to understand me
or even like me.

1202
01:10:44,507 --> 01:10:45,821
This is business.

1203
01:10:47,890 --> 01:10:49,261
Not anymore.